      "lesson title": "Personalised Learning Systems: Bias in Education",
      "order": 1,
      "Description": "Personalised learning systems use data and algorithms to tailor educational experiences to individual students, but when the underlying data is flawed or incomplete, these systems can reinforce existing inequalities rather than reduce them. This lesson introduces the key risks associated with biased data in education, exploring how factors such as socioeconomic background, race, and gender can become embedded in automated decision-making. You will look at real-world examples of how unequal learning paths can emerge when systems rely on historical patterns that reflect past disadvantage rather than genuine potential. By the end of this lesson, you will have a clearer understanding of why it is important to question the data that drives personalised learning tools and how to spot the warning signs of bias in practice.",
